<LP>
   AMHERST, N.Y. -- Mark IV Industries Inc. said it acquired
Vapor Corp., a unit of Brunswick Corp., for $39.5 million.
Vapor, with annual sales of $66 million, is the largest
manufacturer of door systems for rail, rail transit and bus
vehicles in the U.S. and Canada. Mark IV is a diversified
manufacturer.
