   Business Brief -- Oregon Steel Mills Inc.
   Company Planning to Offer
   2.5 Million Shares to Public
</HL>
<DATE>
12/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 27
</SO>
<CO>
   OS
</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Oregon Steel Mills Inc. said it plans a public offering of
2.5 million shares. Proceeds will be used to repay short-term
bank debt, fund capital expenditures and for other general
corporate purposes, which may include working capital and
acquisitions.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
the Portland, Ore., company said the offering will be managed
by Merrill Lynch &amp; Co. and PaineWebber Inc., and includes an
option that allows the underwriters to purchase as many as
375,000 additional shares for covering any over allotments,
if any.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In composite trading Monday on the New York Stock
Exchange, Oregon Steel's stock closed at $22.25 a share, down
$1.75.
   Oregon Steel produces steel plate and large-diameter steel
pipe and has facilities in Portland, Ore., and Fontana and
Napa, Calif.
